{{! Operator-board visual orientation lives on the freestyle landing page; the
    glossary's role here is terminology and execution detail, not visual taxonomy. }}

<p class="glossary-compositional-layering-note">
  Each modifier layered onto a base introduces a <em>simultaneous additional
  constraint</em> on body motion within a single set cycle. Difficulty therefore
  scales not linearly with modifier count, but through the interaction of
  multiple constraints. Two modifiers on a base are usually harder than the
  sum of their parts would suggest; the body has to satisfy both
  mechanics at once.
</p>
<p>A trick is typically composed of:</p>
<pre><code>set &rarr; modifiers &rarr; base &rarr; catch (stall or kick)</code></pre>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Base trick</strong>: the core motion (e.g. mirage, whirl).</li>
  <li><strong>Modifiers</strong>: how the trick is altered (e.g. paradox, spinning).</li>
  <li><strong>Set</strong>: how the trick begins.</li>
</ul>
<p>Examples:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Paradox Whirl = whirl (base) + paradox (modifier).</li>
  <li>Ripwalk = butterfly (base) + stepping (modifier).</li>
</ul>
<p>The glossary explains terms; the dictionary defines exact structure.</p>
<p class="detail-muted">
  Some modifier weights have varied historically by era, region, and judge;
  the values below reflect the current Wave-1 ratified consensus. For the
  full accounting and discrepancy cases see
  <a href="/freestyle/add-analysis">ADD Accounting &amp; Analysis</a>.
</p>

{{! Movement-system axes preamble: surfaces the axis ontology before the
    modifier cards so readers see the system at a glance. }}
<h3 class="section-heading" id="movement-system-axes">Movement-system axes</h3>
<p>
  Modifiers cluster along four educational axes by what timing layer
  and body system they engage. The
  <a href="/freestyle/tricks?view=movement-system"><em>By Movement System</em> dictionary view</a>
  groups tricks by axis; the modifier cards below are listed in
  cluster-paired form to surface the same structure.
</p>
<ol class="glossary-movement-system-axes">
  <li><strong>Set / Uptime Systems</strong>: launch mechanics + uptime dex character.<br>
    <em>pixie, fairy, atomic, quantum, nuclear, barraging, furious, blurry, stepping, whirling</em>.</li>
  <li><strong>Entry Topologies</strong>: entry relationship and cross-body framing.<br>
    <em>paradox</em>; positional vocabulary (op/ss, near/far, x-dex) lives in &sect;3 and &sect;7.</li>
  <li><strong>Midtime Body Modifiers</strong>: apex body mechanics around the trick&apos;s peak.<br>
    <em>spinning, ducking, diving, weaving, zulu, inspinning, gyro, tapping</em>.</li>
  <li><strong>No-Plant &amp; Suspension</strong>: body-discipline mechanics; the support leg leaves the ground.<br>
    <em>symposium, symple, muted, flying</em>.</li>
</ol>
<p class="detail-muted">
  The cards below surface a curator-selected pedagogical cohort
  (13 cards across 2 visual clusters); the full axis breakdown
  lives on the dictionary&apos;s movement-system browse surface.
</p>

